## Remediation Roadmap (Prioritized with tickets)
Action must be taken within the next 7 days to eliminate the immediate threat.

Urgency | Ticket ID | Finding | Action Required (Nonâ€‘Negotiable Implementation)
--- | --- | --- | ---
P0 (Immediate) | SEC-RCE-002 | LFI â†’ RCE | IMMEDIATELY disable LFI vectors. Enforce server-side Whitelisting for file parameters and block path traversal sequences (../).  
P0 (Immediate) | SEC-POLP-001 | Running as Root | IMMEDIATELY reconfigure the web server to run with an unprivileged service account (e.g., www-data). Conduct a full PoLP audit across all services.  
P1 (Short-Term) | SEC-WEB-003 | Exposed Version | Implement custom error pages and proxy settings to suppress all server and application version headers.  
P2 (Long-Term) | SEC-DEV-001 | Insecure Design | Conduct a comprehensive source code audit to identify and fix all instances of implicit trust in user-supplied input.

